<h2>Content block</h2>
<p>The block works on its own and uses standard page typography when it is not inside an Easy Read content wrapper.</p>

{{#>_docs-example}}
{{>_easy-read-block model.easy-read-1}}
{{/_docs-example}}

<h2>Easy Read page typography</h2>
<p>Wrap a complete Easy Read page or section in <code>nsw-easy-read-content</code>. The wrapper applies the Easy Read type scale without changing the rest of the site.</p>

{{#>_docs-example}}
<div class="nsw-easy-read-content">
  {{>_easy-read-block model.easy-read-2}}
  {{>_easy-read-block model.easy-read-3}}
</div>
{{/_docs-example}}

<h2>Decorative image</h2>
<p>Only mark an image as decorative when it adds no information. The component then renders an empty <code>alt</code> attribute.</p>

{{#>_docs-example}}
{{>_easy-read-block model.easy-read-5}}
{{/_docs-example}}

<h2>About Easy Read</h2>

{{#>_docs-example}}
